* Install GIT
sudo apt-get update012
sudo apt-get install git

* Install jdk java
http://www.2daygeek.com/how-to-install-java-7-openjdk-on-ubuntu/

* Config python 3.4

Edit file ~/.bash_aliases and put
alias python='python3'
* Install virtualenvwrapper

http://virtualenvwrapper.readthedocs.org/en/latest/

1. sudo apt-get install python-pip

2. sudo pip install virtualenvwrapper

3. mkvirtualenv --python=/usr/bin/python3 nameOfEnvironment

4. pip install django

5. Check 

>>> import django
>>> print(django.get_version())

* Install PostgreSQL
http://www.enterprisedb.com/crossover-thankyou
Al archivo .run darle permisos de ejecuci√≥n

install sudo apt-get build-dep python-psycopg2
pip install psycopg2 

* Init migrate BD
python manage.py migrate

*Subir proyecto

touch README.md
git init
git add README.md
git commit -m "comentario"
git remote add origin https://github.com/LuchoCastillo/Repositorio.git
git push -u origin master

* Crear migraciones por app
python manage.py makemigrations contest

*Instalar Node para luego usar bower
sudo apt-get install nodejs
sudo npm install -g bower
sudo ln -s /usr/bin/nodejs /usr/bin/node